1
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,333
<i> Every night,</i>

2
00:00:12,467 --> 00:00:16,800
<i>I find myself hoping you were
the one lying next to me.</i>

3
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:18,833
<i>Miss Jade's plan didn't push
through.</i>

4
00:00:18,967 --> 00:00:19,800
<i> Emma is safe.</i>

5
00:00:19,933 --> 00:00:21,200
<i> I'm struggling.</i>

6
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:23,067
<i>I'm sorry, Manang,
but I can't do that.</i>

7
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:25,733
<i>Did something happen between you
and Danilo?</i>

8
00:00:25,867 --> 00:00:28,133
<i>What did she do to you
for you to hurt her again?</i>

9
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:33,167
<i>This woman was so busy spreading
her legs for my fiancé!</i>

10
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:35,267
<i>I've been controlling myself not
to hit you!</i>

11
00:00:37,267 --> 00:00:40,167
<i>I'm sorry that I can't
reciprocate</i>

12
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:42,000
<i> the love you're giving me.</i>

13
00:00:42,133 --> 00:00:45,433
<i>I'll move out once we get back
to Manila.</i>

14
00:00:45,567 --> 00:00:47,967
<i> I want to keep our friendship.</i>

15
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:48,833
<i> So, no.</i>

16
00:00:48,967 --> 00:00:50,267
<i> You're not leaving my house.</i>

17
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:53,300
<i>Are you and Dan going to have
a heart-to-heart talk?</i>

18
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:57,767
<i>Do you think I asked her
to stay here for nothing?</i>

19
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,067
It's already raining.

20
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:41,067
- Hurry up.
- Wait! It's them!

21
00:01:41,233 --> 00:01:41,833
Jade!

22
00:01:41,967 --> 00:01:46,067
- Jade! Hey!
- Jade! Hey!

23
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:49,233
- Can we hitch a ride with you?
- It's raining.

24
00:01:49,367 --> 00:01:51,100
What are you doing here?

25
00:01:51,233 --> 00:01:54,467
Don't tell me you'll also
make a scene like Emma did?

26
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:59,367
Olive, is that you?

27
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:00,600
She's right.

28
00:02:00,733 --> 00:02:03,467
That so Olive Caparas.

29
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:06,067
Friends, I'm so sorry.

30
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,167
It's just that...

31
00:02:08,467 --> 00:02:11,400
our staycation went awry.

32
00:02:11,533 --> 00:02:12,733
Olive, my dear.

33
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:16,600
Hi, Uncle Wiro and Aunt Kutsy.

34
00:02:16,733 --> 00:02:18,300
Mookie.

35
00:02:20,567 --> 00:02:23,867
I think we came
at the wrong time.

36
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,033
Looks like everyone is so tense.

37
00:02:28,333 --> 00:02:32,100
No, it's just that everything
didn't go as planned.

38
00:02:32,233 --> 00:02:35,400
Our supposedly happy family
bonding turned out

39
00:02:35,533 --> 00:02:37,167
to be a disaster.

40
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:39,533
<i> You're so beautiful, Olive.</i>

41
00:02:39,667 --> 00:02:42,100
<i>My daughter,
you take after your mother.</i>

42
00:02:42,233 --> 00:02:44,767
<i>She's right.
Your face looks so gentle.</i>

43
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:46,433
<i> You're like me,</i>

44
00:02:46,567 --> 00:02:51,167
<i>who no one would think is hiding
a demon within.</i>

45
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:53,567
I'm sorry, Wiro and Kutsy.

46
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:55,200
We're all really tired.

47
00:02:55,333 --> 00:02:56,833
If it's okay with you, guys,

48
00:02:56,967 --> 00:02:59,700
I'm inviting you tomorrow
for a late lunch.

49
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:02,867
Mookie will come home early
from school tomorrow.

50
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,100
Right, baby girl?

51
00:03:05,133 --> 00:03:06,000
Yes.

52
00:03:06,133 --> 00:03:08,000
You don't have to do that.

53
00:03:08,133 --> 00:03:09,467
<i> You are Mookie.</i>

54
00:03:10,633 --> 00:03:13,000
<i>Your grandmother's description
of you was spot on.</i>

55
00:03:14,233 --> 00:03:16,700
<i>I can see kindness in your face.</i>

56
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:19,600
Sorry if we visited
at the wrong time.

57
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:22,667
We only want to know if you have
any news about Ligaya.

58
00:03:24,333 --> 00:03:26,533
Tomorrow, late lunch.

59
00:03:26,667 --> 00:03:27,500
See you.

60
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:33,533
Kutsy, Wiro, I'm sorry.

61
00:03:33,667 --> 00:03:36,567
- Let's go.
- It's okay, Danilo.

62
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:38,967
- Let's go.
- Bye. Be safe.

63
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:40,400
- Be safe.
- We will.

64
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:50,400
<i>Why don't we go straight
to Danilo and Mookie?</i>

65
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:52,900
<i> We can't do that, Ador.</i>

66
00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:55,400
<i> Mookie might get harmed, too.</i>

67
00:03:55,567 --> 00:03:59,300
<i>Olive might take her anger out
on her.</i>

68
00:04:02,733 --> 00:04:04,267
I wonder what she'll serve
for us tomorrow.

69
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:05,167
I know.

70
00:04:05,300 --> 00:04:06,367
We don't usually have a late
lunch.

71
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:07,933
We always have an early lunch,
right?

72
00:04:08,067 --> 00:04:10,800
- Yes.
- What about our ride?

73
00:04:10,933 --> 00:04:12,967
I've booked it already.
He's on his way here.

74
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:13,700
Okay.

75
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:17,400
But you know what, Kutsy?

76
00:04:17,533 --> 00:04:19,767
Jade is so weird.

77
00:04:19,900 --> 00:04:21,700
Sometimes, she seems okay.

78
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,233
Sometimes, she's like a monster.

79
00:04:23,367 --> 00:04:24,033
Just like earlier.

80
00:04:25,067 --> 00:04:25,867
What was that?

81
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:26,833
True.

82
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:31,600
She really was like Olive.

83
00:04:31,733 --> 00:04:34,900
Exactly!

84
00:04:35,033 --> 00:04:37,467
Remember what Ligaya said?

85
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:40,767
<i> You know, I was so surprised.</i>

86
00:04:40,900 --> 00:04:42,967
<i>She acted like a completely
different person from Jade.</i>

87
00:04:44,233 --> 00:04:46,333
<i> We noticed that, too.</i>

88
00:04:46,467 --> 00:04:50,067
<i>We thought Jade was a good
person.</i>

89
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:54,233
<i>When she yelled at me,
she reminded me of Olive.</i>

90
00:04:56,133 --> 00:04:57,133
Yes.

91
00:04:57,267 --> 00:04:58,500
Could it be that she is...

92
00:04:59,933 --> 00:05:02,467
Oh, come on, Cuz.
Don't egg me on.

93
00:05:02,633 --> 00:05:04,333
I'm thinking the same thing.

94
00:05:04,467 --> 00:05:05,733
She's Olive.

95
00:05:05,867 --> 00:05:10,700
And she knows why Ligaya
is still missing in action.

96
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:12,033
True!

97
00:05:12,167 --> 00:05:16,800
Maybe that's why she seems
to avoid it whenever

98
00:05:16,933 --> 00:05:18,067
someone brings up Ligaya.

99
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:23,867
But we don't have proof.
All we have is suspicion.

100
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,733
Tomorrow.

101
00:05:24,867 --> 00:05:26,567
Tomorrow at her late lunch
party,

102
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:29,867
we'll bombard her with questions
about Ligaya.

103
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,033
Right!

104
00:05:31,167 --> 00:05:32,033
That's right.

105
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:36,200
Someone seems to be following
us.

106
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,300
Jade's following us.

107
00:05:38,433 --> 00:05:39,667
Let's run! Now!

108
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:41,900
Where's our ride?

109
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:43,500
Wait. Here you go.

110
00:05:43,633 --> 00:05:45,533
- Manong!
- Get in the car.

111
00:05:45,667 --> 00:05:47,967
- Manong! Hurry up!
- Drive faster!

112
00:05:49,167 --> 00:05:53,167
Wait! Wait! Wait!

113
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:57,333
Wiro, Kutsy.

114
00:05:58,633 --> 00:06:00,133
I need your help.

115
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:12,100
Mommy, are you okay?

116
00:06:13,967 --> 00:06:15,033
No, I'm not.

117
00:06:17,367 --> 00:06:19,267
Did you hear what the doctor
said?

118
00:06:20,867 --> 00:06:23,733
My stomach hurt
because of stress.

119
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,967
I couldn't help but get stressed
when I found out

120
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:29,667
that you and Emma spent
the night together.

121
00:06:30,733 --> 00:06:33,900
Tell me, did something happen
between the two of you?

122
00:06:34,933 --> 00:06:36,867
Did you let her seduce you?

123
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:40,233
Did you believe her lies?

124
00:06:40,367 --> 00:06:42,567
Dad, something happened
between you and Mom?

125
00:06:45,133 --> 00:06:47,000
Damn you, Danilo!

126
00:06:47,133 --> 00:06:49,367
Damn you!
How could you do this to me?

127
00:06:49,767 --> 00:06:51,733
- How could you do this to me?
- Jade, sorry!

128
00:06:54,867 --> 00:06:56,367
I still love Emma.

129
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:57,533
What?

130
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,533
I'll understand
if you'll get mad at me.

131
00:07:08,100 --> 00:07:12,633
You can curse me all your life
and deny me forgiveness,

132
00:07:12,767 --> 00:07:17,067
- No! No! No!
- I never stopped loving her.

133
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:18,400
No!

134
00:07:19,767 --> 00:07:21,633
Damn you!

135
00:07:21,767 --> 00:07:24,300
Emma left you!

136
00:07:24,433 --> 00:07:27,567
She left you for another man.
You and Mookie!

137
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:31,067
She left you for Logan.

138
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:35,900
You and Mookie hate me
because you thought

139
00:07:36,033 --> 00:07:38,333
something was going on between
me and Logan.

140
00:07:38,467 --> 00:07:39,567
Even if there's none.

141
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:44,067
I heard that they're not having
an affair, Jade.

142
00:07:45,567 --> 00:07:47,467
So, Mom was telling the truth.

143
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,300
That she and Logan are not
in a relationship?

144
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:52,567
Yes, dear.
They're not having an affair.

145
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:56,767
So we should talk to your mom
to clear things out.

146
00:07:57,933 --> 00:07:58,667
No!

147
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:02,833
I won't let you talk to Emma.

148
00:08:02,967 --> 00:08:05,533
You will never see her again!

149
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:09,600
Jade, sorry, but you can't tell
me and Mookie what to do.

150
00:08:09,733 --> 00:08:10,300
No.

151
00:08:10,433 --> 00:08:12,267
I know I made a mistake.

152
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:15,800
I'm sorry, but I'm calling
the wedding off.

153
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:21,833
No! No! No, Danilo!
This can't be!

154
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:24,500
You can't do this to me!

155
00:08:24,633 --> 00:08:26,300
We have already given out
our invitation.

156
00:08:26,433 --> 00:08:27,633
The guests already knew about
it.

157
00:08:27,767 --> 00:08:29,567
There's no way I'm letting you
embarrass me!

158
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:30,900
- No!
- Jade!

159
00:08:31,033 --> 00:08:33,600
- No, you can't do this to me!
- I will never change my mind!

160
00:08:33,733 --> 00:08:35,833
No! No! No! Danilo, please.

161
00:08:35,967 --> 00:08:39,433
- I'm canceling the wedding!
- Don't do this to me, Danilo!

162
00:08:39,567 --> 00:08:41,700
I'm begging you. No, love!

163
00:08:41,833 --> 00:08:42,633
Love!

164
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:45,567
Mookie!

165
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:46,733
Mookie, dear!

166
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:48,167
Please help me.

167
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:49,833
Please help me convince
your father

168
00:08:49,967 --> 00:08:51,967
that he's making a big mistake.

169
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:55,233
- Please help me, Mookie.
- I'm sorry, Mommy.

170
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:57,467
I can't help you.

171
00:08:57,600 --> 00:09:01,033
I don't think I can ever change
Dad's mind.

172
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,400
You really are ungrateful!

173
00:09:06,467 --> 00:09:08,133
It's not often that I ask you
for a favor,

174
00:09:08,267 --> 00:09:10,033
and you still won't help me!

175
00:09:10,167 --> 00:09:12,533
After everything I did for you!

176
00:09:17,867 --> 00:09:19,367
I'm so sorry.

177
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:20,733
I'm so sorry.

178
00:09:20,867 --> 00:09:24,200
I can't bear losing your father.

179
00:09:24,333 --> 00:09:25,300
No!

180
00:09:25,433 --> 00:09:26,233
No!

181
00:09:26,367 --> 00:09:27,233
Danilo!

182
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,500
Danilo, wait!

183
00:09:35,767 --> 00:09:37,967
<i> Because you disobeyed me...</i>

184
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:40,767
<i> I'm everything you've got!</i>

185
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:43,967
<i> You ungrateful child!</i>

186
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:46,933
<i> You're ungrateful!</i>

187
00:09:47,067 --> 00:09:51,800
<i>I sacrificed everything
just to raise you, Mookie!</i>

188
00:09:51,933 --> 00:09:53,600
<i> I gave you everything!</i>

189
00:09:55,633 --> 00:10:02,700
<i> There! You want this? Eat it!</i>

190
00:10:02,867 --> 00:10:06,400
<i>You will be like a living doll.</i>

191
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:12,333
<i> My living doll.</i>

192
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:23,167
Mooks!

193
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:24,500
Mooks, wait.

194
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:30,200
Why are you avoiding me again?

195
00:10:32,567 --> 00:10:34,833
Zayn, you know why. Right?

196
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:40,000
Your mom might find out
that we're still friends.

197
00:10:40,133 --> 00:10:44,033
I let you come with us even if
I know you only made an excuse.

198
00:10:44,167 --> 00:10:46,733
Mooks, we're at school.

199
00:10:48,533 --> 00:10:50,333
But Stacy's still lurking.

200
00:10:51,433 --> 00:10:56,400
She might see us talking
and let your mom know.

201
00:10:56,533 --> 00:10:57,367
Okay.

202
00:10:57,500 --> 00:10:58,900
I'm only worried, Mooks.

203
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:00,900
You're not replying
to my messages.

204
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:02,400
So tell me what happened.

205
00:11:04,367 --> 00:11:06,500
It's so chaotic, Zayn.

206
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:08,267
My dad called off the wedding.

207
00:11:08,433 --> 00:11:09,867
What?

208
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:15,500
Mommy Jade yelled at me
because she was so furious.

209
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:18,233
For a moment, I thought
she was Mommy Olive.

210
00:11:18,367 --> 00:11:22,500
The glare in her eyes,
the way her jaws trembled...

211
00:11:22,633 --> 00:11:24,933
she really reminded me
of Mommy Olive.

212
00:11:25,067 --> 00:11:26,567
Really?

213
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:31,300
Don't tell me you think
Aunt Jade is your Mommy Olive?

214
00:11:31,433 --> 00:11:32,767
That's impossible, Mooks.

215
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:34,733
Aunt Jade is way too cool.

216
00:11:37,067 --> 00:11:38,667
So what will you
and Uncle Danilo do?

217
00:11:39,733 --> 00:11:43,267
We'll talk to Mom.

218
00:11:43,433 --> 00:11:46,167
And we're moving out
of Mommy Jade's house.

219
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:47,967
Will your parents get back
together?

220
00:11:49,100 --> 00:11:53,067
It depends on how our
conversation will turn out.

221
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:57,167
But, Zayn, I hope they get back
together.

222
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:59,633
So that our family we'll be
whole again.

223
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,467
Love?

224
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:10,567
Love?

225
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:12,733
Love!

226
00:12:12,867 --> 00:12:15,833
Love, please! Please, love!
Don't leave me, please!

227
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:20,767
Don't do this.
Please, don't leave me!

228
00:12:20,900 --> 00:12:23,200
Jade, you drove Emma crazy!

229
00:12:23,333 --> 00:12:25,267
That's not true!

230
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:27,067
I didn't drive her crazy.

231
00:12:28,667 --> 00:12:29,867
She's my sister.

232
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,800
Why would I do that?

233
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:34,400
I don't hate Emma.

234
00:12:34,533 --> 00:12:36,800
I'm not like Olive.

235
00:12:36,933 --> 00:12:41,400
Emma is my sister. I love her.
I can't do that to her.

236
00:12:41,533 --> 00:12:44,800
She's just fooling us, Love.
Believe me.

237
00:12:44,933 --> 00:12:49,000
She only wants to mess with us.
Please, don't leave me.

238
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:50,333
Please!

239
00:12:50,467 --> 00:12:52,833
Please, don't do this to me.

240
00:12:52,967 --> 00:12:55,300
Love! Love! Please!

241
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:59,400
Those times that Emma was away,

242
00:12:59,533 --> 00:13:01,700
who was there for you
and Mookie?

243
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:04,100
Who took care of you?

244
00:13:04,233 --> 00:13:07,100
Who took you in?
Who gave you love?

245
00:13:08,233 --> 00:13:11,300
I even helped you find her.

246
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:14,100
Who grieved with you?

247
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:15,700
Isn't that me?

248
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:21,567
And now you believe Emma's lies
about me?

249
00:13:21,733 --> 00:13:24,233
Will you abandon me
just like that?

250
00:13:26,167 --> 00:13:28,800
I might get depressed.

251
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:31,933
I might get depressed.
I might get lonely.

252
00:13:32,067 --> 00:13:36,600
I might harm myself if I get
depressed.

253
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:37,400
Jade.

254
00:13:37,533 --> 00:13:38,567
You know me.

255
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:42,000
You know what I'm capable of.

256
00:13:42,133 --> 00:13:44,967
You know what I can do
to myself.

257
00:13:49,667 --> 00:13:51,667
I don't have a reason
to live anymore.

258
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:56,167
I don't have a reason
to breathe!

259
00:13:56,333 --> 00:14:00,367
So it's probably better
for me to be gone!

260
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:03,200
- Perhaps I should end my life!
- Jade, Jade, Jade, Jade!

261
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:05,933
I'm done!

262
00:14:06,067 --> 00:14:09,767
Don't try to threaten me by
hurting yourself.

263
00:14:09,900 --> 00:14:10,967
It's not a threat!

264
00:14:12,167 --> 00:14:16,100
I tried many times to end
my life when I was in Japan.

265
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:20,233
I used to hurt myself.

266
00:14:20,367 --> 00:14:23,700
I got drunk,
I drove under the influence.

267
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:25,533
Because I was miserable.

268
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:30,033
Because I was all alone!

269
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:38,400
I was away from my loved ones.
From Olive.

270
00:14:38,533 --> 00:14:41,667
Back then I was so scared.

271
00:14:44,567 --> 00:14:46,900
But when you came
into my life...

272
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:48,100
You and Mookie...

273
00:14:48,233 --> 00:14:49,733
I've had someone in my life.

274
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:53,600
I've had a family.

275
00:14:55,133 --> 00:14:57,233
I'm not alone anymore.

276
00:14:59,667 --> 00:15:02,233
So please...

277
00:15:03,933 --> 00:15:06,833
Please, I'm begging you.

278
00:15:06,967 --> 00:15:12,633
Danilo, please. Don't leave me.
Please...

279
00:15:12,767 --> 00:15:14,333
Please...

280
00:15:14,467 --> 00:15:15,367
Sorry, Jade,

281
00:15:18,533 --> 00:15:20,133
I've made up my mind.

282
00:15:21,967 --> 00:15:23,700
I made my decision.

283
00:15:23,833 --> 00:15:26,900
What did I do?

284
00:15:27,033 --> 00:15:29,700
What did I do wrong?

285
00:15:29,833 --> 00:15:31,400
Am I not enough?

286
00:15:31,533 --> 00:15:35,533
Is the love I gave you
not enough?

287
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:38,067
Is everything I did
for you not enough?

288
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:44,433
You spent one night with Emma,

289
00:15:44,567 --> 00:15:47,033
and you forgot everything
I did for you.

290
00:15:47,167 --> 00:15:48,233
Just like that!

291
00:15:50,900 --> 00:15:52,567
Tell me.

292
00:15:55,933 --> 00:15:57,800
Did you ever love me?

293
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:19,700
Why is this happening to me?

294
00:16:23,667 --> 00:16:29,667
Why does every man I love
ends up hurting me?

295
00:16:33,333 --> 00:16:35,100
You know what?

296
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:38,067
They kill me with their words.
But you!

297
00:16:39,867 --> 00:16:41,367
Your silence, it's...

298
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,167
It's killing me.

299
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:48,567
Please...

300
00:16:49,733 --> 00:16:51,967
- Please...
- Jade, sorry.

301
00:16:55,467 --> 00:16:57,700
It's not my intention
to hurt you.

302
00:17:05,267 --> 00:17:06,567
Fine.

303
00:17:08,867 --> 00:17:10,733
If you made up your mind.

304
00:17:12,467 --> 00:17:15,600
Then go ahead, I won't stop you.

305
00:17:17,167 --> 00:17:18,500
But please,

306
00:17:20,467 --> 00:17:24,367
don't leave me right away.

307
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:30,000
Let me get a hold of myself.
Do it gently.

308
00:17:32,167 --> 00:17:32,967
Please,

309
00:17:34,633 --> 00:17:37,967
if I have done something good
for you and Mookie.

310
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:41,367
The least that you can do
is prepare me for the pain.

311
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:44,533
Please, do it gently.

312
00:17:44,667 --> 00:17:46,733
Don't drop me like this.

313
00:17:50,633 --> 00:17:51,633
Okay, fine.

314
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:58,067
We won't leave right now.

315
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,433
But I'm moving to the other
room,

316
00:18:03,567 --> 00:18:05,300
so you can get used
to sleeping alone.

317
00:18:05,433 --> 00:18:06,933
Without me.

318
00:18:10,267 --> 00:18:12,433
And then Mookie
and I are leaving.

319
00:18:35,367 --> 00:18:40,000
<i>You actually believed
that I would hurt myself.</i>

320
00:18:40,133 --> 00:18:44,133
<i>Danilo, you're such a good man.</i>

321
00:18:44,267 --> 00:18:47,200
<i>That's your most beautiful
trait.</i>

322
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:50,567
<i>But also your biggest weakness.</i>

323
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:55,100
<i>And I will use that to keep you
from leaving me.</i>

324
00:19:08,467 --> 00:19:10,033
After you're done with that,
can you wipe those jars?

325
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:14,733
And those glasses, too, okay?
Thank you.

326
00:19:14,867 --> 00:19:17,133
Get those dust off.

327
00:19:20,100 --> 00:19:22,167
Hey, what's up?

328
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:23,633
Did he call you yet?

329
00:19:23,767 --> 00:19:25,333
Not yet.

330
00:19:25,467 --> 00:19:30,133
He still hasn't called you?
How are you going to talk?

331
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:32,367
How are you going to get
things clear between you?

332
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:36,333
That's a big problem, Emma.

333
00:19:39,067 --> 00:19:40,833
I have an idea.

334
00:19:40,967 --> 00:19:42,867
Why don't you call him?

335
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:47,700
I didn't get his new phone
number.

336
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:51,900
You didn't get it? Why?
Did you play hard-to-get?

337
00:19:52,033 --> 00:19:55,633
My gosh, so what now?
You're waiting for his call?

338
00:19:55,767 --> 00:19:56,767
You're waiting for nothing.

339
00:19:58,567 --> 00:20:00,167
Maybe you should calm down.

340
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:01,467
We never know.

341
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:04,233
Danilo might still be looking
for a perfect romantic spot.

342
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:05,700
To meet with you.

343
00:20:07,300 --> 00:20:09,200
Or Jade got to him.

344
00:20:11,267 --> 00:20:12,867
I wanted to say
that you're wrong.

345
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:16,100
But Jade is good at that.

346
00:20:16,233 --> 00:20:19,033
She has complete control over
Danilo.

347
00:20:19,167 --> 00:20:23,000
She must have a doctorate
in manipulation.

348
00:20:23,133 --> 00:20:25,667
Or perhaps she has a strong
connection with Satan.

349
00:20:25,800 --> 00:20:26,867
They're best friends.

350
00:20:46,767 --> 00:20:49,633
<i> Please, I'm begging you.</i>

351
00:20:49,767 --> 00:20:51,700
<i> Danilo, please...</i>

352
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:55,400
<i> Don't leave me. Please...</i>

353
00:20:55,533 --> 00:20:57,300
<i> please...</i>

354
00:20:57,433 --> 00:20:58,300
<i> Sorry, Jade.</i>

355
00:21:01,300 --> 00:21:02,933
<i> I made up my mind.</i>

356
00:21:14,133 --> 00:21:18,133
<i>Danilo, haven't I love you
enough?</i>

357
00:21:18,267 --> 00:21:20,400
<i>Is everything I did for you not
enough?</i>

358
00:21:23,033 --> 00:21:24,700
<i> You've been good to me, Jade.</i>

359
00:21:25,833 --> 00:21:28,733
<i>You did everything
to make me happy.</i>

360
00:21:28,867 --> 00:21:29,833
<i> But...</i>

361
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:34,500
<i>I prayed hard for us
to have a child.</i>

362
00:21:34,633 --> 00:21:36,233
<i> And you will be the best mom.</i>

363
00:21:36,367 --> 00:21:38,933
<i>Our child will be so lucky
to have you as her mom.</i>

364
00:21:39,067 --> 00:21:41,400
<i> I'm happy that we're together.</i>

365
00:21:41,533 --> 00:21:44,100
<i>I'm happy with whatever we have.</i>

366
00:21:44,267 --> 00:21:46,800
<i>Don't worry,
I'll be with you.</i>

367
00:21:46,933 --> 00:21:48,933
<i> I'll be with you till the end.</i>

368
00:21:50,833 --> 00:21:51,733
<i> Forgive me, Jade.</i>

369
00:21:52,967 --> 00:21:54,467
<i> I loved you, too.</i>

370
00:21:56,167 --> 00:21:57,700
<i> But I love Emma more.</i>

371
00:21:59,167 --> 00:22:02,233
<i>No matter how hard
I tried to love you.</i>

372
00:22:03,267 --> 00:22:04,767
<i> I'm still in love with her.</i>

373
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:16,500
Hello?

374
00:22:18,700 --> 00:22:19,600
Danilo?

375
00:22:32,367 --> 00:22:33,567
Hello?

376
00:22:33,700 --> 00:22:34,567
Leticia.

377
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:36,600
What are you doing?

378
00:22:36,733 --> 00:22:38,733
Why am I hearing clatters?

379
00:22:38,867 --> 00:22:41,867
I'm preparing a late lunch
for Wiro and Kutsy.

380
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:45,000
Danilo's low-life friends.

381
00:22:45,133 --> 00:22:47,467
You're taking care of those
peasants, too?

382
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:50,167
Well, I don't really
have a choice.

383
00:22:50,333 --> 00:22:54,333
I need to be friends with
the people that surround him.

384
00:22:54,467 --> 00:22:56,167
<i> And who knows...</i>

385
00:22:56,300 --> 00:23:00,167
maybe I'll be able to use those
peasants to my advantage.

386
00:23:00,767 --> 00:23:04,500
A little bribe, a little gift,

387
00:23:04,633 --> 00:23:07,000
and I'm sure
they will be my allies.

388
00:23:14,567 --> 00:23:15,800
Danilo's about to leave.

389
00:23:16,833 --> 00:23:18,667
I have a feeling he's going
to meet with Emma.

390
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:19,733
What?

391
00:23:19,867 --> 00:23:20,967
Stop him from leaving!

392
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:23,267
Don't give them a chance
to talk and see each other.

393
00:23:23,433 --> 00:23:26,333
Jade, that will be the end
of you.

394
00:23:26,467 --> 00:23:27,700
Okay, bye, I have to go.

395
00:23:30,467 --> 00:23:31,767
Where are you going?

396
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:33,267
I'm going to see Danilo.

397
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:34,567
I won't let you!

398
00:23:34,700 --> 00:23:35,733
Logan, please.

399
00:23:35,867 --> 00:23:37,600
Danilo and I need to talk.

400
00:23:37,733 --> 00:23:39,700
No one can say no to Logan.

401
00:23:39,833 --> 00:23:41,433
No one can tell me no!

402
00:23:41,567 --> 00:23:44,067
Wait, what are you going
to tell him?

403
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:45,933
I don't know.
I'm probably gonna crash my car

404
00:23:46,067 --> 00:23:48,400
so he'll feel bad for me and
bring me to the hospital.

405
00:23:48,533 --> 00:23:50,433
What?

406
00:23:50,567 --> 00:23:52,033
Why did my car stop?

407
00:23:52,167 --> 00:23:53,767
Wait, Sir. I'm getting on.

408
00:23:55,633 --> 00:23:56,700
Hey!

409
00:23:56,833 --> 00:23:58,267
Didn't you see me about
to get on?

410
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:00,600
You beat me to my seat.
What kind of man are you?

411
00:24:00,733 --> 00:24:02,500
Hello, Danilo.
Where are you?

412
00:24:02,633 --> 00:24:04,633
I'm close by.

413
00:24:08,767 --> 00:24:11,700
I can't lose you again.
